Another great feature is Rise Stimulation*. The Rise Stimulation button continuously increases the stimulation level until the button is released. This allows you to hold the Rise button until you notice a response from the dog, essentially allowing the dog to choose the appropriate level of stimulation. Prior to the Rise Stimulation, dog trainers had to guess at the correct stimulation level for individual dogs. With Rise Stimulation, the dog responds to a level that matches his temperament. title: For Sale:  Colt M16A1 US Property Marked Transferable M16
postcontent: Selling an unbelievable find, one of the few US Property marked transferable M16's in the United States. This is an all factory original machine gun that was built by Colt in Hartford, CT in the late 1970's. This was sold to the Federal Government, and the widely accepted story is that these were issued to the Department of Energy (DOE) to protect nuke sites across the country. A small number of these were sold to civilians in the late 1980's.As you can see, this was a carried weapon and has some great patina and lots of character. It is so hard to find a M16 with honest wear - it is actually much harder than finding a new one. This rifle mechanically is in excellent condition including the bore. It appears to have been fired very little. One of the things that attracts me to this rifle is with the US Property markings, it is 'the very thing' for so many different military builds that you could do, like a MK18 Mod 0 build, or a MK12 SPR build, this is the exact lower - it wouldn't even be a clone.
